claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table showing demographic and clinical characteristics of participants (age 18–64) receiving egg-based and cell-based influenza vaccines, including sex, ethnicity, preexisting conditions (asthma, diabetes, COPD, coronary heart disease), and prior-year vaccination status, followed by text summarizing relative vaccine effectiveness outcomes. does not support the claim because the table and accompanying text present participant characteristics and vaccine effectiveness results but contain no data or statements about mutations arising during production or their impact on vaccine effectiveness. Note: Analysis limited to visible content; low resolution prevents reading some small text but no mention of production mutations was discernible.
